<item>
            <title>[AMQ-1177] ActiveMQConnection memory leaks</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-1177</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;klas eriksson: Commented on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-847&quot; title=&quot;Memory Leaks&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;AMQ-847&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;AMQ-847&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think this issue is actually two (or more memory leaks.&lt;br/&gt;
One in createConnection() and one in close().&lt;br/&gt;
I tried a very similar program with the following results:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;apache-activemq-4.2-incubator-20061204.023752-14:&lt;br/&gt;
1. &apos;createConnection&apos; followed by &apos;close&apos; when activeMq-server is UP:&lt;br/&gt;
outOfmemory after ~1800 createConnection-close.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. &apos;createConnection&apos; without close when activeMq server is not started.&lt;br/&gt;
outOfmemory after &amp;lt; 1800 failed &apos;createConnection&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have also tried 4.0.x and 4.1.x. The leak memory too.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
